Regular sports bar with a dive kinda feel but the food here is amazing and the service from the ladies working the bar and tables are top notch. I forgot our servers name unfortunately 🤦‍♂️but she gave some great recommendations on what to eat. It has a modern up to date jukebox as well. Parking was right in front. I enjoyed it.

Great place to enjoy sports events. TVs everywhere so you have a great view from any seat. But the outstanding feature is the awesome waitresses. One of them went out of her way to find me a seat with the best access to A/C when I told her I am always hot, even though I saw she was busy when I entered. Even sat me a table with my own personal fan blowing on me because she said she was the same. And they all were attentive and anticipatory to my needs without being overbearing. Great pupus, I had the ribeye steak with onions, made to order and seasoned to perfection. Perfect companion to the ice cold Stella Artois! This is my go-to spot for UFC.

my experience at cafe anasia is almost too great for words . as soon as you walk in your greeted by kind and loving people, stay there for 5 minutes and you'll feel right at home! after having a few drinks we were hungry and decided to order food let me tell you it surpassed any expectations i had , the chef truly has a passion for cooking and even makes it a point to come and make sure your happy with the food. he's somehow infused meals from different parts of the world and made it bar appropriate  but believe me when i say this is NO bar food ! this place is a must  rather you wanna catch a game , play some darts , or just grab a drink and bite to eat cafe anasia is the place to be ! (* make sure you order the crab and crawfish)

Came here a couple of times recently after a long hiatus and was pleasantly surprised at the quality of the new food menu. Steak was well cooked and seasoned well, pork chops were a little dry but good flavors, summer roll comes with sausage which I thought was weird but ended up being really good. Beer pitchers are still cheap. The lot that used to be the old union headquarters is not a Hocu bank and is a paid lot that you download an app for your phone to pay. Pretty reasonable though. Or else look for street parking like usual if the small lot in front is full.
